How this connects to your Google Colab project

From your recent work, you've already built most of a RAG pipeline:

PyMuPDF → Extracts text from watch PDFs.
Text Chunking → Splits the PDF into smaller sections.
SentenceTransformer (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) → Converts each chunk into embeddings.
FAISS → Stores and searches those embeddings efficiently.
Gemini/OpenAI API → Receives the retrieved chunks and generates a natural-language answer.

So when your user asks, "Show Titan watches under ₹5,000 with a leather strap," the system does not search the entire PDF line by line.
It searches the vector database for the most relevant chunks, then lets the LLM generate a clear, conversational answer. 
This is the core idea your instructor is introducing in the "Why RAG?" lesson.

