Step 2: What is an LLM?

LLM = Large Language Model

Examples

GPT-4
GPT-5
Gemini
Claude
Llama

The LLM predicts the next most likely word.

Example

Input

India is famous for ______

The model predicts

cricket

or

spices

or

culture

based on probability.

This is what your instructor wrote as "continuous prediction."

=======

Step 3: Why ChatGPT Can Answer Questions

ChatGPT uses an LLM.

The process is

User

↓

ChatGPT

↓

OpenAI API

↓

GPT Model

↓

Predict Next Tokens

↓

Answer

The model does not search Google every time. It answers based on what it learned during training (unless tools like RAG or web search are added).

======

Step 4: The Problem with Only an LLM

Imagine you ask:

What is Sugumar Company's leave policy?

The GPT model has never seen your company's private HR policy.

It has only learned general knowledge.

So it might answer:

Most companies provide 12–20 casual leave days.

This is only a guess.

This guessing is called hallucination.

=======

Step 5: Why RAG is Needed

Instead of guessing,

RAG first searches your documents.

User Question

↓

Search Documents

↓

Find Relevant Information

↓

Give Context to LLM

↓

LLM Generates Answer

Now the answer becomes

According to your HR Policy Version 3.2,

Casual Leave = 12 days

Sick Leave = 10 days

This answer comes from your document.

